- "gardeners" refers to the active authors;
- "planted" metaphorically represents contributing topics;
- "more than a dozen blooms" indicates more than 10 topics;
- "unlocked garden beds" corresponds to unlocked and active chapters and sections;
- "active chapters" refers to the active status of documents and chapters.

- "A handful of times" refers to more than 10 accesses; 
- "Substantial amount of content" means the document has over 5000 words; 
- "Gone through at least a few revisions" indicates an average version number greater than 1.
